# Visual Studio / .NET
## Ignore Visual Studio temporary files, build results, and generated files
*.suo
*.user
*.userosscache
*.sln.docstates

# Build results
[Bb]in/
[Oo]bj/
[Rr]elease/
[Dd]ebug/
[Ll]ogs/

# NuGet Packages
*.nupkg
# The packages folder can be ignored because of Package Restore
**/packages/*
# except build/, which is used restoring MSAccess and other tools
!**/packages/build/

# Roslyn files
*.roslynidicache

# Rider
.idea/

# VS Code
.vscode/

# Test results
[Tt]est[Rr]esult*/
[Bb]uild[Ll]og.*
*.VisualState.xml
TestResult.xml

# User-specific files
*. DotSettings.user
*.DS_Store

# SQLite
# Ignore journal files and write-ahead logs
# but DO NOT ignore the main .db file if it's meant to be part of the repo source
# (like our taskmanager.db in the project root).
# If taskmanager.db was ONLY in bin/obj, it would be ignored by the [Bb]in/ [Oo]bj/ rules above.
*-journal
*-wal
*-shm

# Specific to this project if taskmanager.db was *only* a generated output,
# but we want the one in the project root to be committed.
# So, no explicit ignore for taskmanager.db here.